sec.p:
A case study might give practical knowledge back to the field;


“In evidence- based medicine, the case of an individual has been downgraded to the status of an “anecdote,” but in teaching the case study thrives, for it is the best way to communicate practical knowledge to trainees. It is through detailed examples that clinicians come to understand what is involved in illness and treatment.”
(Riessman, 2003, p. 6).
